label chapter5:

    # [Scene: Living Shoreline Pilot Site | Late Morning]

    scene bg ch5_4001e7_1 at full_bg
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Up-tempo rhythmic strings with percussion—energized, driving]
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: Camera shutters, low murmur of reporters, call-and-response chants at the edge of hearing; gulls cutting through the noise]
    "You arrive with peat under your nails and the electric scrape of a thousand small decisions behind your ribs. The site thrums: hands digging, laughter when someone drops a tray of seedlings, a reporter threading a"
    "microphone into the line of work like an eager tide. Sunlight tries to push through a thin, salty haze; brine and new-mown reeds mix into a sharp, honest smell that tastes like promise."
    "Lena is at the waterline, sleeves rolled, sunburn freckling the bridge of her nose. She pulls a rope of native reeds with the economy of someone who has mended nets and lives by knots."

    "Lena" "Here—hold the line, don't pull the root. You'll tear it out if you yank."
    show ari_navarro at left:
        zoom 0.7

    ari_navarro "Like this?"

    "Lena" "Firmer. Think of it as coaxing, not wrestling."
    "A volunteer kid nearby watches you carefully, mud on the soles of his sneakers, eyes bright with the kind of attention that wants a model to copy. You crouch, show him how to cradle a sedge—fingers"
    "under the clump, thumbs steady at the base—and the way his jaw sets is a small, steady tide in your chest."
    "Maya Cruz threads past, carrying a tray of plugs and an infectious grin that turns to a worried line when she sees the cluster of council members by the tarp."
    show maya_cruz at right:
        zoom 0.7

    maya_cruz "Council's poking their heads. A camera crew just asked for an interview. They're waiting on you, Ari—front and center, apparently."
    "You feel the old mechanisms engage: checklist, tone, the careful arithmetic of metrics that can be read aloud in a chamber of fluorescent lights and cameras. But the site's warmth—the smell of turned soil, the squeak"
    "of wet boots—keeps pulling your language away from technocratic cadence and toward the things that matter here: kids, kitchen tables, streets that used to belong to neighbors."
    hide ari_navarro
    hide maya_cruz

    scene bg ch5_4001e7_2 at full_bg
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: A phone vibrates against a fold of waterproof canvas]
    "Sora Watanabe threads through volunteers like a current, theatrical and precise. They plant a hand on a speaker and call attention with a grin that makes people lean in."
    show sora_watanabe at left:
        zoom 0.7

    sora_watanabe "Look—data with feet. This is our proof, not a press release. Let them see it."
    show ari_navarro at right:
        zoom 0.7

    ari_navarro "Let them see, and let them understand what it will mean on the ground."
    "Sora Watanabe's eyes catch yours, and there's a quick, flaring thing—hope braided with impatience."

    sora_watanabe "If the council drags their feet, we'll take the staging yard tonight. Occupy. Make them answer to bodies, not memos."

    ari_navarro "That's a political action, Sora. It has legal fallout, and—"

    sora_watanabe "—and it's what gets headlines and pressure and money moving. We don't have time for slow margins when the models already say some streets will be gone in five years."
    "You find yourself balancing the two halves of your life: the planner who trusts models and process, and the person who once watched people get trapped by a flood because someone delayed. You hear your own heartbeat as a thin rope tightening."

    menu:
        "Step closer and whisper support to Sora Watanabe":
            "Ari Navarro closes the distance. Your voice is low but fierce; Sora Watanabe's smile softens, and for a breath the world narrows to pulse and intention."
        "Stay visible and keep speaking for measured process":
            "Ari Navarro takes a couple of steps back toward the line of volunteers and begins explaining the next metric you need. People listen; the practical cadence steadies the room, but Sora Watanabe's hand finds yours briefly before slipping away."

    menu:
        "Agree to meet Sora Watanabe outside after sundown to plan the occupation":
            "Ari Navarro's nod is small but decisive. Sora Watanabe's relief spills into a grin that reaches their eyes; volunteers glance up, sensing the pivot. The site hums louder, as if more people are ready for a different kind of work."
        "Ask for a written plan now—no occupation until we map the risks":
            "Ari Navarro asks Sora Watanabe to slow. They bristle, but then they breathe, folding the anger into a careful frustration. Dr. Noor gives you a look that says this is the weight of leadership. The crowd quiets into practical planning again."

    jump chapter6
